<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>exFAT last access times were modified despite both <code>ro</code> and <code>noatime</code> mount options. This did not happen before. Perhaps it has something to do with remounting. Also, it has not happened on FAT32 or FAT16 so far.</p> <pre><code>$ mount |grep USB2 /dev/sdi1 on /media/username/USB2 type fuseblk (ro,nosuid,nodev,noatime,user_id=0,group_id=0,default_permissions,allow_other,blksize=4096,uhelper=udisks2) $ ls -l -u --full-time text.txt -rwx------ 1 username usergroup 135 2022-07-22 02:04:37.000000000 +0200 test.txt </code></pre> <p>(Previous last access date was 2022-07-18.)</p> <p>Unbelievable. I can&#39;t even trust &quot;<code>noatime</code>&quot; anymore.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/ThrowAway237s"> /u/ThrowAway237s </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w4w8th/quick_note_exfat_last_access_times_are_also_not/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w4w8th/quick_note_exfat_last_access_times_are_also_not/">[comments]</a></span>